    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-05-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-05-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="994"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d994">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/7653.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to Brazil</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-05-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 31, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>An expression of opinion from the Government of the United States of America
                    regarding the advisability of recognizing the present Government of Mexico would
                    be highly appreciated by the Government of Brazil. Both Argentina and Chile have
                    inquired what action Brazil contemplates. Brazil desires to know whether or not
                    the United States would be incommoded if the three Powers should recognize
                    before the United States found it convenient to do so.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
